ling courts of two global powers that deeply affected the cultures of medieval Europe, Byzantium, Islam, South Asia, and China.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Mai 2022) 0aMonarchyxSocial aspectszIran. 0aMonarchyxSocial aspectszRome. 0aRites and ceremonieszIran. 0aRites and ceremonieszRome. 0aRomansxSocial life and customs. 0aSassanidsxSocial life and customs. 7aHISTORY / Ancient / General.2bisacsh  aancient history.  aancient rome.  aancient societies.  aancient world.  aart.  abyzantium.  achina.  aclassical heritage.  aclassical history.  acourt life.  aengaging.  aeurope.  aglobal politics.  aglobal powers.  ahistorical.  airanian history.  aislam.  akingship.  amedieval europe.  amedieval society.  amedieval times.  anear east.  anonfiction study.  apersian empire.  apivotal period.  apolitical history.  aroman empire.  arome.  aroyal intrigue.  aroyalty.  asacred kingship.  asasanian iran.  asouth asia.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of California Press Backlist Package 2000-2013z978311069042240uhttps://doi.org/10.1525/978052094457240uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780520944572423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780520944572/original  a978-3-11-069042-2  University of California Press Backlist Package 2000-2013c2000d2013  aEBA_FAO  aEBA_UCA_YUP  aGBV-deGruyter-alles